	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
			<br>&nbsp;<u><i><font color="#FFFF00">IN GAME CONTROLS:</font></i></u><br>
                  &nbsp; Move character - 
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;D-Pad or Left Analog Stick</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Jump / Confirm menu commands - 
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;X Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Use selected pocket item / Shoot elemental shot (while wearing an elemental ring) - 
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Triangle Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Attack / Talk / Open doors (note: some towns prohibit the use of weapons so you might not be able to draw your weapon in some places) - 
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Square Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Talk to people / Pick up objects / Put away your sword / Cancel menu commands - 
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Circle Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Slide attack - 
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Circle Button (while running)</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Run - 
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;R2 Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Use pocket item - 
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;L2 Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Change pocket item - 
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;L2 Button + D-Pad</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Rotate camera - 
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;L1 or R1 Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Zoom in and out - 
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Select Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Open item screen / Skip opening movie and cut scenes - 
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Start</font><br>
        &nbsp;</td>
	 </tr>
	</table>
